cql:
library BonnieTestRatio version '0.2.000'

/*CMS872
Patient-based
Scoring=Ratio*/

using QDM version '5.4'

include CalendarCalculations version '1.1.000' called Cal

valueset "Coronary Artery Bypass Graft": 'urn:oid:2.16.840.1.113883.3.464.1003.104.12.1002'
valueset "Ethnicity": 'urn:oid:2.16.840.1.114222.4.11.837'
valueset "Measles Antibody Test (IgG Antibody Titer)": 'urn:oid:2.16.840.1.113883.3.464.1003.198.12.1059'
valueset "ONC Administrative Sex": 'urn:oid:2.16.840.1.113762.1.4.1'
valueset "Payer": 'urn:oid:2.16.840.1.114222.4.11.3591'
valueset "Race": 'urn:oid:2.16.840.1.114222.4.11.836'
valueset "Rubella Antibody Test (IgG Antibody Titer)": 'urn:oid:2.16.840.1.113883.3.464.1003.198.12.1063'

parameter "Measurement Period" Interval<DateTime>

context Patient

define "SDE Ethnicity":
	["Patient Characteristic Ethnicity": "Ethnicity"]

define "SDE Payer":
	["Patient Characteristic Payer": "Payer"]

define "SDE Race":
	["Patient Characteristic Race": "Race"]

define "SDE Sex":
	["Patient Characteristic Sex": "ONC Administrative Sex"]

define "Bypass 10 or more years ago":
	["Procedure, Performed": "Coronary Artery Bypass Graft"] Graft
		where difference in years between start of Graft.relevantPeriod and start of "Measurement Period" > 10

define "Measles Indicator 1":
	["Laboratory Test, Performed": "Measles Antibody Test (IgG Antibody Titer)"] MeaslesTiter
		where MeaslesTiter.result >= 1.10

define "Initial Population":
	exists ["Procedure, Performed": "Coronary Artery Bypass Graft"]

define "Denominator":
	"Initial Population"

define "Numerator":
	exists "Bypass 10 or more years ago"
		and "DaysCriteria"
		and exists "Measles Indicator 1"
		and exists "Rubella Indicator 1"

define "DaysInYearCount":
	Cal."CountOfDaysInYear"(year from start of "Measurement Period")

/*Obviously bogus criteria, just wanted to use a library for UAT*/

define "DaysCriteria":
	"DaysInYearCount" > 360

define "Rubella Indicator 1":
	["Laboratory Test, Performed": "Rubella Antibody Test (IgG Antibody Titer)"] RubellaTiter
		where RubellaTiter.result ~ 1: 8
